India RBI May Intervene to Smoothen Rupee Volatility, CNBC Says

-- B y   H a r i   G o v i n d
-- 
2011-09-23T05:20:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/india-rbi-may-intervene-to-smoothen-rupee-volatility-cnbc-says.html
India ’s central bank may intervene
in the foreign exchange market to “smoothen volatility,”
Deputy Governor  Subir Gokarn  told CNBC television today. The
Reserve Bank of India is not planning any changes to its policy
on rupee management, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
